dc_title_s: Map of a part of the Isthmus of Darien to accompany the paper by M. Lucien de Puydt
dc_description_s: Relief shown by hachures. Pass of Paya or Tanela (discovered Augst. 27, 1865), line of the projected canal of M. L. de Puydt, and route of Andres de Arisa (1785) are shown. Limits of the tide on Chucunaque and Tuyra rivers, major waterfalls, and Gulf of Uraba currents are shown. Territories of the Indians [indigenous groups] are shown. From: The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 38, (1868), pp. 69-110; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.38 1868.
dc_publisher_s: London : published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, by J. Murray, Albemarle Street, 1868.
